<p>I have a VERY simple email form (for a members-only page for a private club) to send email blasts.  The code is simply:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;html&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="../../../tinymce/jscripts/tiny_mce/tiny_mce.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt;  &lt;h1&gt;Email Blast&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;form method="post"&gt;  &lt;input type="hidden" name="from" value="blast@club.com" /&gt; &lt;input type="hidden" name="to" value="blast@club.com" /&gt; &lt;input type="hidden" name="reply" value="from@club.com" /&gt; &lt;input type="hidden" name="bcc" value="Tester &lt;test@club.com&gt;" /&gt;  &lt;label for="subject"&gt;Subject&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;input type="text" name="subject" id="subject" style="width: 600px" /&gt;&lt;br/&gt;  &lt;label for="message"&gt;Message&lt;/label&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;textarea id="message" name="message" rows="15" cols="100" class="tinymce"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;br/&gt;  &lt;br/&gt;&lt;input type="submit" value="Send Email" name="submit"&gt;  &lt;/form&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt; jQuery(document).ready(function() {     tinymce.init({selector:"textarea.tinymce"}); }); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>For some reason the page simply isn't rendering the <code>textarea.tinymce</code> as I would expect, but there are no error messages in the JS Console and all the breakpoints are hit as I would expect.</p>  <p>What am I missing?</p>